The paper deals with connectionist temporal classification (CTC) based supervised sequence training of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for speech and handwritten character recognition, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of GPUs for parallel training, which falls under the category of computer vision (CV) and systems and control (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper introduces an expectation-maximization (EM) based online CTC algorithm, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
